tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant dyslipidemia (high total cholesterol, LDL, triglycerides, and low HDL) and elevated fasting glucose, indicating increased cardiovascular and metabolic risk. Renal function, electrolytes, and hematological parameters are within normal limits. No evidence of microalbuminuria. Recommend clinical correlation for diabetes and cardiovascular risk management.
